  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2007-12-19",
    "date": "2008-04-15T16:03:57Z",
    "text": "Broadcast Licensing in the Public Interest Act - Amends the Communications Act of 1934 to require, as a part of broadcast station license renewal, that a station demonstrate it's dedication to civic affairs, local news, local programming, elections, and educational programming for children.\n\nDecreases the term of new and renewal licenses from eight to three years."
  },
